Description: Oval handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay fine pink-buff. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Pencil '195', circled. Name Aristombrotidas. Trimmed. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0085.26.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1162)
